This version of the theorem is straightforward because it simply uses the property of the norm of the imaginary unit in a complex-like structure, and the `aesop` tactic is sufficient to handle the logical cases. The previous version was more complicated and introduced unnecessary case splits. The corrected version uses `simp` to directly apply the known property `RCLike.norm_I` and then uses `aesop` to resolve any remaining logical implications. 

